================================================================================
ABOUT THIS BENCHMARK
================================================================================
Moondream uses a custom architecture that is not compatible with
bitsandbytes (4-bit/8-bit) quantization due to custom layer implementations.

This benchmark tests PyTorch native quantization methods:
  • FP32 (Full Precision) - Baseline
  • FP16 (Half Precision) - Recommended for deployment
  • INT8 (Dynamic Quantization) - CPU only

⚠️  FP32 test may fail on low VRAM GPUs. Skipping...
If you have >8GB VRAM, you can uncomment the FP32 test in the code.

